<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 10:37PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Potential for Black Ice Overnight...
There is the potential for patchy black ice on untreated surfaces
overnight. An area of light rain and snow is moving across the
New River Valley with temperatures in the 30s. Roads are wet
between Christiansburg, and Bristol Virginia, along the
Interstate 81 corridor. Once the precipitation comes to an end
after midnight, temperatures are expected to dip into the 20s.
This may cause any untreated wet surface to freeze into a thin
layer of ice.
For your safety, if you are traveling overnight, be aware that
roads may become icy, and this hazard may linger through the
Thursday morning commute. Please slow down and allow for extra
travel time for your commute Thursday morning. In addition, be
mindful of sidewalks and steps which may also contain a thin layer
of ice.</description>
